Kenyan special forces were called in from Nairobi to Garissa University College to aid in the massacre . 
  But troops did not arrive at the scene until just before 2pm on Thursday . 
  One of the four gunmen responsible has been identified as the lawyer son of a government official . 
  Government representatives have defended the response time comparing it to being a goalkeeper . 
  148 people were killed in the pre-dawn attack on the university . 
 